name: NDC UN (Unit)
description: A recognized billing qualifier that may be used to identify a unit as the NDC unit of measure. This is often used when describing a powder for injection (needs to be reconstituted), pellet, kit, patch, tablet or device.

name: NDC ME (Milligram)
description: A recognized billing qualifier that may be used to identify milligrams as the NDC unit of measure.

name: NDC GR (Gram)
description: A recognized billing qualifier that may be used to identify a unit as the NDC unit of measure. This is often used when describing ointments, creams, inhalers or bulk powder in a jar.

name: NDC ML (Milliliter)
description: A recognized billing qualifier that may be used to identify a milliliter as the NDC unit of measure. This is often used when describing a liquid, solution, or suspension.

name: NDC F2 (International Unit)
description: A recognized billing qualifier that may be used to identify International Units as the NDC unit of measure. This is often used when describing IU/vial or micrograms.

name: Dose Length Product
description: The product of the number of computed tomography (CT) scans multiplied by the scan width (i.e., total scan length). This value is an indicator of the integrated radiation dose of a specific CT scan. This is expressed in the SI units milligray x centimeters (mGy x cm). DLP is CTDIvol x slice thickness x # of slices.

name: CT Imaging Acquisition Protocol Element CTDI VOL
Microgram per Milliliter
description: A metric unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one gram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic meter. The concept also refers to the metric unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of a substance which mass equal to one gram occupies the volume of one cubic meter.

name: Megavolt
description: A SI derived unit of electric potential and electromotive force that is equal to one million volts.

name: Meter per Second Squared
description: Meter per second squared is a SI unit of acceleration.

name: Reciprocal Meter
description: The SI unit of wave number, the spatial analogue of frequency; closely related to the concept of the wave vector.

name: Cubic Meter
description: A SI unit of volume or capacity equal to the volume of a cube with edges one meter in length. It is equal to 1,000 liters; 1,000 cubic decimeters; 10(e+6) cubic centimeters; 25.3 cubic feet; 6.29 barrels.

name: Meter per Second
description: A SI derived unit of both speed (scalar) and velocity (vector), defined as the distance of one meter travelled per unit time equal to one second.

name: Square Meter
description: A SI unit of area measurement equal to a square whose sides are one meter long. Square meter is equal to 10,000 square centimeters; 0.01 are; 1.196 square yards; 10.76 square feet; 1550 square inches.

name: Katal
description: A unit for measuring catalytic (e.g. enzymatic) activity, the ability of the compound to accelerate the chemical reaction by providing a lower energy pathway between the reactants and the products. One katal is that catalytic activity which will raise the rate of reaction by one mole per second in a specified assay system. When the katal is used, the measurand should be specified by reference to the measurement procedure; the measurement procedure must identify the indicator reaction. The katal is not used to express a rate of reaction itself, which should be expressed in moles per second. Katal is coherent with the SI.

name: Kilogram per Cubic Meter
description: A SI derived unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one kilogram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic meter, or the concentration of one milligram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one milliliter, or one gram of a substance per one liter of the mixture. It is also a unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one milliliter.

name: Cubic Meter per Kilogram
description: A SI derived unit of specific volume, a property of materials defined as the number of cubic meters occupied by one kilogram of a particular substance. Specific volume is inversely proportional to density.

name: Coulomb
description: A SI derived unit of quantity of electricity, equal to the quantity of charge transferred in one second across a conductor in which there is a constant current of one ampere.

name: Volt
description: A SI derived unit of electric potential and electromotive force, equal to the difference of electric potential between two points on a conducting wire carrying a constant current of one ampere when the power dissipated between the points is one watt, equivalent to the potential difference across a resistance of one ohm when one ampere of current flows through it.

name: Pascal
description: A SI derived unit of pressure equivalent to one newton per square meter or 10 bars or to 1.45x10E-4 pounds per square inch.

name: Joule
description: A unit of electrical, mechanical, and thermal energy (as well as work and quantity of heat) in the SI system, equal to the work done when the point of application of a force of one newton is displaced through a distance of one meter in the direction of the force or the work done when a current of one ampere passes through a resistance of one ohm for one second. Joule is equal to 0.23889 gram-calorie (mean).

name: Hertz
description: A SI derived unit of frequency; equal to one oscillation (one cycle) per second.

name: Newton
description: A SI derived unit of force. The force which, when applied in a vacuum to a body having a mass of one kilogram, causes an acceleration of one meter per second squared. It is equal to 10E5 dynes.

name: Radian
description: A SI-derived unit of plane angle measurement defined and named by James Thomson in 1873. One radian is the plane angle between two radii of a circle that cuts off on the circumference an arc equal in length to the radius. There are 2pi radians in a complete circle. SI units: m/m = 1.

name: Steradian
description: A SI derived unit of solid angle measurement. One steradian is the solid angle that, having its vertex in the center of a sphere, cuts off an area on the surface of the sphere equal to that of a square with sides of length equal to the radius of the sphere. It is equal to 0.25 of the solid angle around a point, 0.079 58 sphere, 0.159 16 hemisphere, 0.636 6 spherical right angle, 3,282.8 square degrees. The solid angle corresponding to all of space being subtended is 4pi steradians.

name: Meter
description: A unit of linear measure in the metric system, one of the seven base units of the International System of Units (Systeme International d'Unites, SI). A meter is defined as the length of the path traveled by light in a vacuum during a time interval of 1/299 792 458 of a second and is equal to 1.093 61 yards.

name: Ampere
description: A unit of electric current, one of the seven base units of the International System of Units (Systeme International d'Unites, SI). It is that constant current which, if maintained in two straight parallel conductors of infinite length and zero diameter separated by one meter in a vacuum, would produce between these conductors a force equal to 2x10E7 newton per meter of length. This is dependent upon the definitions of the meter, kilogram, and second. One ampere represents 6.24 x 10E18 unit electric charge carriers, such as electrons, passing a specified fixed point in one second.

name: Kelvin
description: A basic unit of thermodynamic temperature, one of the seven base units of the International System of Units (Systeme International d'Unites, SI). It is 1/273.16th of the thermodynamic temperature of the triple point of water. This sets the size of the kelvin unit for temperature differences and defines the thermodynamic temperature of an equilibrium mixture of waters ice-liquid-vapor as 273.16 K, where 0 K is the lowest possible temperature ("absolute zero").

name: Second
description: A unit of time, one of the seven base units of the International System of Units (Systeme International d'Unites, SI). The second is the duration of 919 263 177 0 periods of the specified light radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the caesium 133 atom in its ground state at 0 K. According to the convention, 60 seconds constitute one minute; 3,600 seconds constitute one hour.

name: Candela
description: A unit of luminous intensity, one of the seven base units of the International System of Units (Systeme International d'Unites, SI). It is the luminous intensity in a given direction of a small monochromatic light source at 540 terahertz emitting 1/683 watt per steradian in that direction. This is dependent upon the definitions of the meter, kilogram, and second.

name: Mole
description: A unit of amount of substance, one of the seven base units of the International System of Units (Systeme International d'Unites, SI). It is the amount of substance that contains as many elementary units as there are atoms in 0.012 kg of carbon-12. When the mole is used, the elementary entities must be specified and may be atoms, molecules, ions, electrons, other particles, or specified groups of such particles.

name: Kilogram
description: A basic SI unit of mass. It is defined as the mass of an international prototype in the form of a platinum-iridium cylinder kept at Sevres in France. A kilogram is equal to 1,000 grams and 2.204 622 6 pounds.

name: Unit of Relative Amount of Substance Content
symbol: Unit of Relative Amount of Substance Content

name: Unit of Catalytic Activity Content
description: A unit used to express catalytic activity of the catalytic component per mass of the system that contains this component.

name: Nanomole per Milligram of Protein
description: A unit of concentration of amount of substance of a component measured in nanomoles of the component per milligram of protein of the mixture.

name: Nanomole per Kilogram
description: Nanomoles per kilogram.

name: Nanomole per Gram
description: Nanomoles per gram.

name: Micromole per Mole
description: A unit of fraction expressed as the ratio of the amount of a substance in solution, in micromoles, to the amount of a different substance in the mixture, in moles.

name: Picomole per Billion Cells
description: A unit of concentration (molarity unit) equal to one picomole of substance per ten to the ninth power cells.

name: Picomole per Ten Billion Cells
description: A unit of concentration (molarity unit) equal to one picomole of substance per ten to the tenth power cells.

name: Nanomole per Mole
description: A unit of fraction expressed as the ratio of the amount of a substance in solution, in nanomoles, to the amount of a different substance in the mixture, in moles.

name: Picomole per Deciliter
description: A unit of concentration (molarity unit) equal to one picomole of solute per deciliter of solution.

name: Picomole per Day
description: A unit of amount of substance flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one picomole of substance travels to a given object or space over a period of time equal to 24 hours.

name: Picomole per Liter per Hour
description: A rate unit expressed in picomole(s) per liter of solution per period of time equal to sixty minutes.

name: Nanomole per Liter per Hour
description: A rate unit expressed in nanomole(s) per liter of solution per period of time equal to sixty minutes.

name: Femtomole per Gram
description: A molality unit that describes the amount of substance, expressed in femtomole(s) per gram.

name: Mole per Milligram
description: A unit of amount of substance content (molality unit) defined as one mole of solute per one milligram of solvent.

name: Mole per Gram
description: A unit of amount of substance content (molality unit) defined as one mole of solute per one gram of solvent.

name: Millimole per Kilogram
description: A unit of amount of substance content (molality unit) defined as one thousandth of mole (10E-3 mole) of solute per one kilogram of solvent.

name: Mole per Kilogram
description: A unit amount of substance content (molality unit) defined as one mole of solute per one kilogram of solvent.

name: Micromole per Kilogram per Minute
description: A unit of concentration (molarity unit) equal to one millionth of a mole (10E-6 mole) per kilogram of a substance per period of time equal to sixty seconds.

name: Million Units
description: A quantity equivalent to one million units (10E6 units).

name: Kilounit
description: A quantity equivalent to one thousand units (10E3 units).

name: Milliunit
description: A quantity equivalent to the one thousandth unit (10E-3 unit).

name: Joule per Kilogram-Kelvin
description: A SI unit of specific entropy.

name: Joule per Kelvin
description: A SI unit of entropy used also as a unit of heat capacity.

name: Joule per Mole-Kelvin
description: A SI unit of molar entropy used also as a unit of molar heat capacity.

name: Joule per Cubic Meter
description: A SI derived unit of energy density defined as the energy equal to one joule stored in the volume equal to one cubic meter.

name: Watt per Meter-Kelvin
description: A SI derived unit of thermal conductivity defined as heat flow rate of one watt in a direction normal to a surface of material, in thickness one meter, due to a temperature difference equal to one degree Kelvin.

name: Bel
description: A logarithmic ratio unit (base-10 logarithms) used to express relative magnitude of a physical quantity (usually power or intensity) in comparison with a specified or implied reference level. Particularly, Bel is used as a unit of relative sound intensity. In the latter context it is equal to ten decibels or to approximately 1.151293 nepers.

name: Decibel
description: A unit of measure representing the intensity of an electrical signal or sound which is equal to ten times the logarithm of the ratio of two signals.

name: Phosphatidylserine IgA Antibody Unit per Milliliter
description: Unit of measure of potency of allergenic product expressed as a number of immunoglobin A phosphatidylserine units per one milliliter of formulation.

name: Phosphatidylserine IgM Antibody Unit per Milliliter
description: Unit of measure of potency of allergenic product expressed as a number of immunoglobin M phosphatidylserine units per one milliliter of formulation.

name: Phosphatidylserine IgG Antibody Unit per Milliliter
description: Unit of measure of potency of allergenic product expressed as a number of immunoglobin G phosphatidylserine units per one milliliter of formulation.

name: Tuberculin Unit per Milliliter
description: A unit of biologic activity of tuberculin expressed as a number of arbitrary units of tuberculin in one milliliter of preparation.

name: Liter Divided by Microgram per Day
description: A unit of concentration equal to one liter divided by the derived denominator microgram per day.

name: Liter Divided by Milligram Per Day
description: A unit of concentration equal to liter per milligram per day.

name: Liter Divided by Milligram per Meter Squared
description: A unit of concentration equal to one liter divided by the derived denominator milligram per square meter.

name: Per Milliliter
description: A volume unit equal to one milliliter used as a denominator to build a derived unit expressed as a ratio. (NCI)

name: Nanomole per Milliliter per Hour
description: Nanomoles per milliliter per hour.

name: Nanogram per Second
description: Nanograms per second.

name: Nanounit per Milliliter
description: Nanounits per milliliter.

name: Picogram per Hour
description: Picograms per hour.

name: Picogram per Day
description: Picograms per day.

name: Picogram per Minute
description: Picograms per minute.

name: Picogram per Second
description: Picograms per second.

name: Milliliter per Mole per Hour
description: Milliliters per mole per hour.

name: Milliliter per Mole per Minute
description: Milliliters per mole per minute.

name: Milliliter per Mole per Second
description: Milliliters per mole per second.

name: Milliliter per Kilogram per Second
description: Milliliters per kilogram per second.

name: Milliliter per Mole per Day
description: Milliliters per mole per day.

name: Milligram per Milliliter per Hour
description: Milligrams per milliliter per hour.

name: Milligram per Second
description: Milligrams per second.

name: Environmental Temperature Units
description: The units of measure that are used to express the temperature of the surroundings.

name: Degree Fahrenheit
description: A unit of temperature of the temperature scale designed so that the freezing point of water is 32 degrees and the boiling point is 212 degrees, placing the boiling and melting points of water 180 degrees apart. One degree Fahrenheit is 5/9ths of a kelvin (or of a degree Celsius), and minus 40 degrees Fahrenheit is equal to minus 40 degrees Celsius.

name: Degree Celsius
description: A unit of temperature of the temperature scale designed so that the freezing point of water is 0 degrees and the boiling point is 100 degrees at standard atmospheric pressure. The current official definition of the Celsius sets 0.01 C to be at the triple point of water and a degree to be 1/273.16 of the difference in temperature between the triple point of water and absolute zero. One degree Celsius represents the same temperature difference as one Kelvin.

name: Kelvin
description: A basic unit of thermodynamic temperature, one of the seven base units of the International System of Units (Systeme International d'Unites, SI). It is 1/273.16th of the thermodynamic temperature of the triple point of water. This sets the size of the kelvin unit for temperature differences and defines the thermodynamic temperature of an equilibrium mixture of waters ice-liquid-vapor as 273.16 K, where 0 K is the lowest possible temperature ("absolute zero").

name: Milliliter of Water
description: A unit of volume of water equal to one millionth (10E-6) of a cubic meter of water, one thousandth of a liter of water, one cubic centimeter of water, or 0.061023 7 cubic inch of water.

name: Drug Vehicle Unit of Volume
description: A unit used to express a volume of a carrier or inert medium in which a medicinally active agent is formulated and/or administered.

name: Fluid Dram British
description: A volume equal to 1/8 Brisith fluid ounce, 0.216 734 cubic inches or 3.551 633 milliliters.

name: Femtoliter
description: The non-SI unit of volume accepted for use with the SI equal to one quadrillionth of a liter (10E-15 liter).

name: Deciliter
description: The unit of volume equal to one tenth of a liter. Accepted for use with the SI.

name: Drop British
description: A unit of volume in British Imperial system equal to 1/36 fluid dram or approximately 99 microliters.

name: Medical Drop
description: A unit of volume equal to approximately 0.08333 milliliter (1 mL = 12 medical drops).

name: Metric Drop
description: A unit of volume used in pharmacy and equal to 0.05 milliliter (20 drops/ml).

name: Cubic Meter
description: A SI unit of volume or capacity equal to the volume of a cube with edges one meter in length. It is equal to 1,000 liters; 1,000 cubic decimeters; 10(e+6) cubic centimeters; 25.3 cubic feet; 6.29 barrels.

name: Attoliter
description: A unit of volume equal to one quintillionth of a liter (10E-18 liter) or one cubic micrometer.

name: Milliliter
description: A unit of volume equal to one millionth (10E-6) of a cubic meter, one thousandth of a liter, one cubic centimeter, or 0.061023 7 cubic inch. A cubic centimeter is the CGS unit of volume.

name: Microliter
description: A unit of volume accepted for use with the SI and equal to one millionth of a liter (10E-6 liter).

name: Fluid Ounce British
description: A traditional unit of liquid volume equal in the British Imperial system to 1/20 pint, or 1.733 871 cubic inches or 28.413 063 milliliters.

name: Gallon British
description: A traditional unit of volume designed to contain 10 pounds of distilled water under precisely defined conditions and equal to 4.546 091 liters, 277.4194 cubic inches, or 1.20095 US liquid gallons, or 1.03206 US dry gallons.

name: Gallon Scotland
description: A traditional unit of volume equal to 4 Scots quarts, or approximately three British Imperial gallons, or 3.6 US liquid gallons, or 13.63 liters.

name: Gallon US
description: The US unit of liquid volume legally defined as 3785.411784 milliliters (3.785 411 784 liters), or 231 cubic inches. The US gallon holds 4 liquid quarts; the gallon of water gallon weighs approximately 8.33 pounds.

name: Gallon Historical
description: A historical British unit of dry volume equal to 4 dry quarts, or 1/8 of a US bushel (Winchester bushel), or 268.8025 cubic inches, or 4404.88377086 milliliters.

name: Quart
description: A United States liquid unit equal to 32 fluid ounces; four quarts equal one gallon.

name: Pint
description: A United States liquid unit equal to 16 fluid ounces; two pints equal one quart.

name: Tablespoon Dosing Unit
description: A unit of volume informally used in pharmacy. Under the metric system the tablespoon has been standardized at 15 milliliters in the US, Britain, Canada, and New Zealand, and at 20 milliliters in Australia and some European countries.

name: Teaspoon Dosing Unit
description: A unit of volume used in pharmacy and equal to 5 milliliters.

name: Liter
description: The non-SI unit of volume accepted for use with the SI. One liter is equal to cubic decimeter, or one thousandth of cubic meter, or 1000 cubic centimeters, or approximately 61.023 744 cubic inches.

name: Billion Organisms
description: A unit of measure of quantity of organisms expressed in billions.

name: Thousand Organisms
description: A unit of measure of quantity of organisms expressed in thousands.

name: Million Organisms
description: A unit of measure of quantity of organisms expressed in millions.

name: Focus Forming Unit
description: A quantitative unit of measure of cell clusters of a specific interest.

name: Million Viral Particles
description: A unit for virus amount measurement that represents a number of viral particles (live and dead combined) expressed in millions.

name: Million Plaque Forming Units
description: A measure of viable infectious entities expressed in millions in the specimen or product defined as the smallest quantity that can produce a cytopathic effect in the host cell culture challenged with the defined inoculum, visible under the microscope or/and to the naked eye as a plaque.

name: Billion Plaque Forming Units
description: A measure of viable infectious entities expressed in billions in the specimen or product defined as the smallest quantity that can produce a cytopathic effect in the host cell culture challenged with the defined inoculum, visible under the microscope or/and to the naked eye as a plaque.

name: Hundred Million Plaque Forming Units
description: A measure of viable infectious entities expressed in hundreds of millions in the specimen or product defined as the smallest quantity that can produce a cytopathic effect in the host cell culture challenged with the defined inoculum, visible under the microscope or/and to the naked eye as a plaque.

name: Ten Million Plaque Forming Units
description: A measure of viable infectious entities expressed in tens of millions in the specimen or product defined as the smallest quantity that can produce a cytopathic effect in the host cell culture challenged with the defined inoculum, visible under the microscope or/and to the naked eye as a plaque.

name: Log10 Plaque Forming Unit
description: A logarithmic-scale (base 10) potency unit for measuring the quantity of individual infectious particles (usually viral particles) based on the number of plaques formed in a cell culture infected with the virus.

name: Lactose Unit
description: A unit of measurement for the activity of lactase enzyme which is expressed as the amount of enzyme that hydrolyzes one microequivalent (uEq) of galactosidic linkage per one minute at a pH of 4.5 and at 37 degrees Celsius.

name: Pock Forming Unit
description: A measure of viable infectious entities (e.g. viral particles or group of particles) in the specimen or product defined as the smallest quantity of a viral suspension that can produce a cytopathic effect in the host chick chorio-allantoic membrane challenged with the defined inoculum, visible under the microscope and/or to the naked eye as a pock.

name: Ten Thousand Colony Forming Units
description: A unit of measurement of viable bacterial numbers equal to 10 to the fourth power colony forming units.

name: Ten Million Colony Forming Units
description: A unit of measurement of viable bacterial numbers equal to 10 to the seventh power colony forming units.

name: Erythroid Colony Forming Unit
description: A unit of viable cell concentration defined as the minimum number of hematopoietic stem cells able to produce a detectable colony of erythroid lineage cells that are past the burst forming stage.

name: Granulocyte-Macrophage Colony Forming Unit
description: A unit of viable cell concentration defined as the minimum number of hematopoietic stem cells able to produce a detectable colony of granulocyte-macrophage lineage cells.

name: Megakaryocyte Colony Forming Unit
description: A unit of viable cell concentration defined as the minimum number of hematopoietic stem cells able to produce a detectable colony of megakaryocyte lineage cells.

name: Erythroid Burst Forming Unit
description: A unit of viable cell concentration defined as the minimum number of hematopoietic stem cells able to produce a detectable colony of erythroid burst forming cells.

name: Colony Forming Unit-Endothelial Cells
description: A population of adherent cells in fibronectin-coated culture that resemble endothelial cells.

name: Billion Colony Forming Units
description: A unit of viable cell quantity equal to 10E9 colony forming units (10E9 CFU).

name: Million Colony Forming Units
description: A unit of measurement of viable cell quantity equal to 10E6 colony forming units (10E6 CFU).

name: Thousand Colony Forming Units
description: A unit of viable cell quantity equal to 10E3 colony forming units (10E3 CFU).

name: Business Day
description: Any day a government or commercial enterprise is open and actively engaged in the work of that enterprise.

name: Weekday
description: Any day other than Saturday and Sunday.

name: Study Day of Cardiovascular System Findings
description: The study day that a cardiovascular system assessment is performed.

name: Planned Study Day of Clinical Encounter
description: The planned study day of a clinical encounter relative to the sponsor-defined reference start date.
symbol: Planned Study Day of Clinical Encounter

name: Study Day of Respiratory System Findings
description: The study day that a respiratory system assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Skin Response Assessment
description: The day that a skin response assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Morphology Assessment
description: The day that a morphology assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Microscopic Findings
description: The day that a microscopic findings assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Subject Status
description: The day that a subject status assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Reproductive System Findings
description: The day that a reproductive system findings assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Immunogenicity Specimen Assessment
description: The study day that an immunogenicity specimen assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Death Diagnosis
description: The study day that a death diagnosis assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Comment
description: The study day that the comment pertains.

name: Study Day of Macroscopic Findings
description: The study day that a macroscopic findings assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Food and Water Consumption
description: The study day that the food and water consumption data is captured.

name: Study Day of Body Weight Gain
description: The study day that a body weight gain assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Body Weight
description: The study day that a body weight assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Clinical Observations
description: The study day that a clinical observation is made.

name: Study Day of Tumor Findings
description: The study day that a tumor findings assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Palpable Masses
description: The study day that a palpable masses assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Organ Measurements
description: The study day that an organ measurements assessment is performed.

name: Cardiovascular System Findings End Day
description: The final day of the cardiovascular system assessment.

name: Healthcare Encounters End Day
description: The final day of the healthcare encounter assessment.

name: Respiratory System Findings End Day
description: The final day of the respiratory system assessment.

name: Procedure End Day
description: The final day of the procedure.

name: Laboratory Test Results End Day
description: The final day of the laboratory test.

name: ECG Test Results End Day
description: The final day of the electrocardiographic test.

name: Food and Water Consumption End Day
description: The final day of the food and water consumption assessment.

name: Body Weight Gain End Day
description: The final day of the body weight gain assessment.

name: Pharmacokinetic Concentration End Day
description: The final day of the pharmacokinetic concentration assessment.

name: Vital Signs End Day
description: The final day of the vital signs assessment.

name: Substance Use End Day
description: The day of the week substance usage concluded.

name: Concomitant Medication Use End Day
description: The day of the week that concomitant medication usage ended.

name: Adverse Event End Day
description: The day of the week that an adverse event concluded.

name: Exposure End Day
description: The day of the week an exposure concluded.

name: Exposure as Collected End Day
description: The final day of the exposure collection period.

name: Subject Visit End Day
description: The day of the week a subject visit has concluded.

name: Birth Day
description: The day of the week on which a person was born.

name: Visit Day
description: The day of the week of a visit.

name: Tumor Findings Dosing Days to Detection
description: The number of days from the start of dosing to the earliest detection of cancer.

name: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation Start
description: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation began.
symbol: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation Start

name: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation Start
description: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation was scheduled to begin.
symbol: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation Start

name: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation End
description: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation was scheduled to end.
symbol: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation End

name: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation
description: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation was scheduled to occur.
symbol: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation

name: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation End
description: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation ended.
symbol: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation End

name: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation
description: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation occurred.
symbol: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation

name: Mortality Cut-off Year, National Death Index
description: The last year of data used in the National Death Index.
symbol: Mortality Cut-off Year, National Death Index

name: Birth Month
description: The month in which a person was born.

name: Month-Day-Year
description: A format of a date in time, with the month followed by the date followed by the year.

name: Week
description: Any period of seven consecutive days.

name: Geometric Mean Fluorescence Intensity Unit
description: A unit of measure for the geometric mean fluorescence intensity.

name: Arithmetic Mean Fluorescence Intensity Unit
description: A unit of measure for the arithmetic mean fluorescence intensity.

name: Relative Fluorescence Intensity Unit
description: A unit of measurement that estimates the size or amount of material in a sample by normalizing its luminescence to that of a reference standard.

name: Normalized Fluorescence Intensity Unit
description: A relative fluorescence intensity unit that is adjusted to a reference standard.

name: Median Fluorescence Intensity Unit
description: A unit of measure equal to the median fluorescence intensity of a log-normal distribution of fluorescence signals.

name: Arbitrary Fluorescence Units
description: Arbitrary unit(s) of fluorescent luminescence.

name: Molecule of Equivalent Soluble Fluorochrome
description: A unit of measure of the fluorescence intensity of a fluorochrome-labeled sample, which is equivalent to the fluorescence intensity of a solution containing an equivalent number of molecules of free fluorochrome in solution, under identical experimental conditions.

name: Candela per Square Meter
description: A unit of luminous intensity expressed as one candela per square meter of area.

name: Candela Second per Square Meter
description: A unit of luminous intensity expressed as one candela in one second of light emittance per square meter of area.

name: Lumen
description: A SI derived unit of luminous flux. It is the amount of light that falls on a unit area at unit distance from a source of one candela.

name: Lux
description: A SI derived unit of illuminance equal to the direct illumination on a surface that is everywhere one meter from a uniform point source of one candela; a unit of illuminance that is equal to one lumen per square meter.

name: Relative Luminescence Unit
description: An arbitrary unit used to measure the intensity of the emitted light from a sample; it is dependent on instrument and measurement parameters.

name: Watt
description: A SI unit of power equal to the power which in one second produces or transfers the energy of one joule. The unit is used in measurements of power emitted, transferred or received as radiation, sound waves, heat flow rate, and rate of energy transfer.

name: Cubic Meter per Kilogram
description: A SI derived unit of specific volume, a property of materials defined as the number of cubic meters occupied by one kilogram of a particular substance. Specific volume is inversely proportional to density.

name: Cup Equivalent
description: A unit of relative amount of a substance equal to one cup.

name: Ounce Equivalent
description: A unit of relative amount of a substance equal to one ounce.

name: Teaspoon Equivalent
description: A unit of relative amount of a substance equal to one teaspoon.

name: Unit of Height
description: An indication of the type of unit of measure being used to express a height.

name: Survey Foot
description: A unit of length defined by the U.S. Metric Act of 1866 as 1200/3937 meter, or approximately 30.48006096 centimeters. This unit is used for geodetic purposes by the United States Public Land Survey System.

name: Foot British
description: A traditional unit of length equal to 30.479976 centimeters, used before 1959 when the unified international definitions for units of British Imperial system were established.

name: International Foot
description: A traditional unit of length defined by the U.S. National Bureau of Standards as 30.48 centimeters. It is equal to 0.3048 meter, 12 inches, or to approximately 0.999998 survey foot.

name: Kilometer
description: A metric unit of distance equal to 1000 meters, 0.621 miles, 1094 yards, or 3281 feet.

name: Mile British
description: A traditional unit of distance equal to 5280 feet of Old British Imperial System, used before 1959 when the unified international definitions for units of British Imperial system were established.

name: Mile
description: A traditional unit of distance equal to 5280 international feet, 1760 international yards, or 1609.344 meters.

name: Survey Mile
description: A traditional unit of distance equal to 5280 survey feet or to approximately 1609.347 meters. This unit is used for geodetic purposes by the United States Public Land Survey System.

name: Femtometer
description: A metric unit of length equal to one quadrillionth of a meter (10E-15 meter).

name: Picometer
description: A metric unit of length equal to one trillionth of a meter (10E-12 meter).

name: Centimeter
description: A basic unit of length in the former CGS version of metric system, equal to one hundredth of a meter or approximately 0.393 700 787 inch.

name: Micron
description: A unit of length in metric system equal to 10E-6 meter, or micrometer.

name: Step Unit of Distance
description: A unit of measure to quantify the number of strides taken during a normal walking gait.

name: Block Unit of Distance
description: A unit of measure to quantify the number of rectangular areas in a city surrounded by streets that the patient has traveled.

name: Millimeter
description: A metric unit of length equal to one thousandth of a meter (10E-3 meter) or approximately 0.03937 inch.

name: Nanometer
description: A metric unit of length equal to one billionth of a meter (10E-9 meter). Nanometer is used as a unit for light wavelength measurement.

name: Meter
description: A unit of linear measure in the metric system, one of the seven base units of the International System of Units (Systeme International d'Unites, SI). A meter is defined as the length of the path traveled by light in a vacuum during a time interval of 1/299 792 458 of a second and is equal to 1.093 61 yards.

name: Inch British
description: A traditional unit of length equal to 2.539998 centimeters, used before 1959 when the unified international definitions for units of British Imperial system were established and inch was defined as 2.54 centimeters.

name: Survey Inch
description: A unit of length equal to international inch/0.999998 or approximately to 2.54000508001016002032004 centimeters.

name: Inch
description: A traditional unit of length equal to 1/12 of a foot or 2.54 centimeters.

name: Decimeter
description: The metric unit of length equal to one tenth of a meter.

name: Lap
description: One circuit around a track or course.

name: Microinch
description: A traditional unit of linear measurement equal to one-millionth of an inch.

name: Milli-Inch
description: A traditional unit of linear measurement equal to one-thousandth of an inch.

name: Picogram Per Cell
description: A unit of mass concentration for the number of picograms of substance per cell.

name: Pen Gram Protein
description: A measure of the amount (in grams) of amino acids prescribed for parenteral and enteral therapy.

name: Troy Pound
description: The non-SI unit of mass equal to 0.3732417216 kg.There are 12 apothecaries ounces, or 240 pennyweight, or 5760 grains in the Troy pound.

name: Pennyweight
description: The non-SI unit of mass equal to 24 grains, 1/20 Troy ounce or approximately 1.5552 gram.

name: Kilopound
description: The non-SI unit of mass equal to 453,592 37 kg.

name: Attogram
description: The metric unit of mass equal to one a quintillionth of a gram (10E-18 gram).

name: Femtogram
description: The metric unit of mass equal to one quadrillionth of a gram (10E-15 gram).

name: Decigram
description: The metric unit of mass equal to one-tenth of a gram.

name: Centigram
description: The metric unit of mass equal to one hundredth of a gram.

name: Yoctogram
description: The metric unit of mass equal to one a septillionth of a gram (10E-24 gram).

name: Zeptogram
description: The metric unit of mass equal to one a sextillionth of a gram (10E-21 gram).

name: Kilodalton
description: A unit of atomic mass equal to one thousand daltons.

name: Unified Atomic Mass Unit
description: The non-SI unit of mass in terms of which the masses of individual atoms and molecules are expressed. Unified atomic mass unit is defined as one twelfth of the mass of an unbound atom of the carbon-12 nuclide, the predominant isotope of carbon, at rest and in its ground state. It is equal to 1.6606x10(E-27) kg (approximately).

name: Troy Ounce
description: The non-SI unit of mass equal to 31.103 grams, 20 pennyweight, or 480 grains, or 0.083 pound.

name: Picogram
description: The metric unit of mass equal to one trillionth of a gram (10E-12 gram).

name: Dram Mass Unit
description: The non-SI unit of mass equal to 1/16 Avoirdupois ounce or 1/256 Avoirdupois pound. One dram equals approximately 1.7718451953125 grams.

name: Apothecaries Scruple
description: The non-SI unit of mass equal to 20 grains or 1.295 978 2 grams.

name: Apothecaries Dram Mass Unit
description: The non-SI unit of mass equal to 60 grains, 3 scruples, 1/8 troy ounce, or approximately 3.8879 grams.

name: Milligram
description: A metric unit of mass equal to one thousandth of a gram or 1000 micrograms. One milligram equals approximately 0.015 432 grain or 35.274 x 10E-6 ounce.

name: Kilogram
description: A basic SI unit of mass. It is defined as the mass of an international prototype in the form of a platinum-iridium cylinder kept at Sevres in France. A kilogram is equal to 1,000 grams and 2.204 622 6 pounds.

name: Microgram
description: A metric unit of mass equal to one millionth of a gram or one thousandth of a milligram.

name: Hour per Day
description: A unit of measurement equal to the number of hours within a period of time equal to one day.

name: Minute per Day
description: A unit of measurement equal to the number of minutes within a period of time equal to one day.

name: Centisecond
description: A unit of time equal to one hundredth of a second (10E-2 seconds).

name: Kilosecond
description: A unit of time equal to one thousand seconds (10E3 seconds).

name: Business Day
description: Any day a government or commercial enterprise is open and actively engaged in the work of that enterprise.

name: Weekday
description: Any day other than Saturday and Sunday.

name: Study Day of Cardiovascular System Findings
description: The study day that a cardiovascular system assessment is performed.

name: Planned Study Day of Clinical Encounter
description: The planned study day of a clinical encounter relative to the sponsor-defined reference start date.
symbol: Planned Study Day of Clinical Encounter

name: Study Day of Respiratory System Findings
description: The study day that a respiratory system assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Skin Response Assessment
description: The day that a skin response assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Morphology Assessment
description: The day that a morphology assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Microscopic Findings
description: The day that a microscopic findings assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Subject Status
description: The day that a subject status assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Reproductive System Findings
description: The day that a reproductive system findings assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Immunogenicity Specimen Assessment
description: The study day that an immunogenicity specimen assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Death Diagnosis
description: The study day that a death diagnosis assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Comment
description: The study day that the comment pertains.

name: Study Day of Macroscopic Findings
description: The study day that a macroscopic findings assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Food and Water Consumption
description: The study day that the food and water consumption data is captured.

name: Study Day of Body Weight Gain
description: The study day that a body weight gain assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Body Weight
description: The study day that a body weight assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Clinical Observations
description: The study day that a clinical observation is made.

name: Study Day of Tumor Findings
description: The study day that a tumor findings assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Palpable Masses
description: The study day that a palpable masses assessment is performed.

name: Study Day of Organ Measurements
description: The study day that an organ measurements assessment is performed.

name: Cardiovascular System Findings End Day
description: The final day of the cardiovascular system assessment.

name: Healthcare Encounters End Day
description: The final day of the healthcare encounter assessment.

name: Respiratory System Findings End Day
description: The final day of the respiratory system assessment.

name: Procedure End Day
description: The final day of the procedure.

name: Laboratory Test Results End Day
description: The final day of the laboratory test.

name: ECG Test Results End Day
description: The final day of the electrocardiographic test.

name: Food and Water Consumption End Day
description: The final day of the food and water consumption assessment.

name: Body Weight Gain End Day
description: The final day of the body weight gain assessment.

name: Pharmacokinetic Concentration End Day
description: The final day of the pharmacokinetic concentration assessment.

name: Vital Signs End Day
description: The final day of the vital signs assessment.

name: Substance Use End Day
description: The day of the week substance usage concluded.

name: Concomitant Medication Use End Day
description: The day of the week that concomitant medication usage ended.

name: Adverse Event End Day
description: The day of the week that an adverse event concluded.

name: Exposure End Day
description: The day of the week an exposure concluded.

name: Exposure as Collected End Day
description: The final day of the exposure collection period.

name: Subject Visit End Day
description: The day of the week a subject visit has concluded.

name: Birth Day
description: The day of the week on which a person was born.

name: Visit Day
description: The day of the week of a visit.

name: Tumor Findings Dosing Days to Detection
description: The number of days from the start of dosing to the earliest detection of cancer.

name: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation Start
description: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation began.
symbol: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation Start

name: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation Start
description: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation was scheduled to begin.
symbol: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation Start

name: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation End
description: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation was scheduled to end.
symbol: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation End

name: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation
description: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation was scheduled to occur.
symbol: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation

name: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation End
description: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation ended.
symbol: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation End

name: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation
description: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation occurred.
symbol: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation

name: Per Millisecond
description: A unit of time, which is equal to the reciprocal of one thousandth of a second.

name: Square Millisecond
description: A unit of time which is equal to one thousandth of a second squared.

name: Hour
description: A unit measure of time equal to 3,600 seconds or 60 minutes. It is approximately 1/24 of a median day.

name: Millisecond
description: A unit of time equal to one thousandth of a second (10E-3 second).

name: Second
description: A unit of time, one of the seven base units of the International System of Units (Systeme International d'Unites, SI). The second is the duration of 919 263 177 0 periods of the specified light radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the caesium 133 atom in its ground state at 0 K. According to the convention, 60 seconds constitute one minute; 3,600 seconds constitute one hour.

name: Decade
description: A period of 10 years.

name: Seconds Per Hour
description: A rate unit expressed in seconds per period of time equal to sixty minutes.

name: Minute
description: A unit measure of time equal to 60 seconds.

name: Picosecond
description: A unit of time equal to one trillionth of a second.

name: Nanosecond
description: A unit of time equal to one billionth of a second.

name: Mortality Cut-off Year, National Death Index
description: The last year of data used in the National Death Index.
symbol: Mortality Cut-off Year, National Death Index

name: Birth Month
description: The month in which a person was born.

name: Month-Day-Year
description: A format of a date in time, with the month followed by the date followed by the year.

name: Week
description: Any period of seven consecutive days.

name: Second Trimester
description: The period of gestation that ranges from the 13th to the 27th week of pregnancy.

name: Late Third Trimester
description: The period of gestation generally corresponding to the last half of the third trimester.

name: Early Third Trimester
description: The period of gestation generally corresponding to the first half of the third trimester.

name: First Trimester
description: The period of gestation that ranges from the first day of the last menstrual period in a woman up to the 12th week of her pregnancy.

name: Semester
description: Half a year; a period of 6 months.

name: Gram per Deciliter
description: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one gram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one deciliter (100 milliliters). The concept also refers to the metric unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one gram occupies the volume one deciliter.

name: Microgram per Milliliter
description: A metric unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one gram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic meter. The concept also refers to the metric unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of a substance which mass equal to one gram occupies the volume of one cubic meter.

name: Kilogram per Liter
description: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one kilogram of a substance in unit volume of the mixture equal to one liter. The concept also refers to the unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one kilogram occupies the volume one liter.

name: Kilogram per Cubic Meter
description: A SI derived unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one kilogram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic meter, or the concentration of one milligram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one milliliter, or one gram of a substance per one liter of the mixture. It is also a unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one milliliter.

name: Milligram per Deciliter
description: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one milligram of a substance in unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic deciliter or 100 cubic centimeters. It is also a unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one cubic deciliter or 100 cubic centimeters.

name: Microgram per Liter
description: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one microgram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one liter. The concept also refers to the unit of mass density (volumetric mass) defined as the density of a substance which mass equal to one microgram occupies the volume of one liter.

name: Microgram per Deciliter
description: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one microgram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one deciliter. The concept also refers to the unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one microgram occupies the volume one deciliter.

name: Gram per Microliter
description: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one gram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one microliter. The concept also refers to the unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one gram occupies the volume one microliter.

name: Picogram per Deciliter
description: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one picogram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one deciliter. The concept also refers to the unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of a substance which mass equal to one picogram occupies the volume of one deciliter.

name: Nanogram per Liter
description: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one nanogram of a substance per one liter of the mixture, or one picogram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one milliliter, or one microgram of a substance per one cubic meter of the mixture. The concept also refers to the metric unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of a substance which mass equal to one nanogram occupies the volume of one liter.

name: Nanogram per Deciliter
description: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one nanogram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one deciliter. The concept also refers to the unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one nanogram occupies the volume of one deciliter.

name: Gram Per Unit
description: A unit of concentration or mass density equal to one gram of substance per unit(s) of substance.

name: Pound per Gallon
description: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one pound of a substance in unit volume of the mixture equal to one gallon. The concept also refers to the unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one pound occupies the volume one gallon.

name: Nanometer
description: A metric unit of length equal to one billionth of a meter (10E-9 meter). Nanometer is used as a unit for light wavelength measurement.
